         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botan. Garden ¶ 14/1/67 ¶ Dear Capt. Standish. ¶  ¶ The old Police horse, which you most kindly granted to my ¶  ¶ deparment ¶  ¶ for use some years ago, is gradually wearing out, and as my ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.01.14<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Frederick Standish</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">P67/732, unit 298, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne botan. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">14/1/67</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Capt. Standish.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The old Police horse, which you most kindly granted to my<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">deparment</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for use some years ago, is gradually wearing out, and as my departmental votes are so heavily taxed as to admit of no purchase of another horse, I venture to ask, whether it would be possible to exchange the horse for an other,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">sic — two words.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">Not uncommon in M's letters</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(just under 400 instances</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">, probably do not sic</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>such as would not be capable of performing any longer the arduous services of the police. The horse we had through your kindness is exclusively used as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">Messanger</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>horse, the errands being often so distant in the service, that for the sake of economising time I have to keep one animal for the messenger use in the establishment,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain, my dear Captain, your very regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'M 189 referred to the Honble the Chief Secretary. The Director of the Botanical Gardens was supplied with an old Police Horse on a former occasion with sanction of the Chief Secretary. If Mr<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">McCuloch</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>approves, I can supply Dr Mueller with one<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">of the our</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>condemned horses who would no doubt answer the purpose for wh<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #00FF00; ">[sic?]</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he is required. The horse formerly handed on to Dr Mueller by the Departments has been turned out in the Police paddock at Dandenong; he is quite worn out. Fredk C Standish C C Police 16-1-67'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The application was marked ' Appd J McC' [Approved, John McCulloch] and forwarded to Standish on 21.1.67.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Standish replied: 'Noted and returned. A suitable horse has been supplied to Dr Mueller Fredk C. Standish C. C. P. 30/1/67 [<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; ">what is this symbol?]</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>769'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">I doubt that we should use<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; background-color: #00FF00; ">sic</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-weight: bold; color: #C00000; ">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>here; not unusual in such minutes.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
